  "statement": "# Partition Labels\n\nSplit a string into as many parts as possible so each letter appears in at most one part.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: s = ababcbacadefegdehijhklij\nOutput: [9,7,8]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: s = eccbbbbdec\nOutput: [10]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: s = abc\nOutput: [1,1,1]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Track the local choice that leaves the most room for future choices, or sort intervals so conflicts can be resolved with one pass.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def partitionLabels(self, s):\n        last = {ch: i for i, ch in enumerate(s)}\n        out = []\n        start = end = 0\n        for i, ch in enumerate(s):\n            end = max(end, last[ch])\n            if i == end:\n                out.append(end - start + 1); start = i + 1\n        return out\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Sort first when relative order drives the decision.",
    "Keep the smallest state that proves future feasibility."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def partitionLabels(self, s):\n        pass\n"
  },
